               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1414" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1414" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1414" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1414" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM CLARK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of my mother, Catherine Clark, and live at Woolwich—about twelve o'clock on the 27th of Oct. I missed a piece of bacon—Mr. Drew gave me a description of the man who took it—I saw the prisoner go into a public-house—I ran to the policeman and told him—I found the bacon in the public-house—it was cooked.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1415" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1415" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1415" type="surname" value="DREW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1415" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN DREW</persName>
                  </hi>. I am assistant to Mr. Stewart, a druggist—I saw the pri<lb></lb>soner take a piece of bacon from Mr. Clark's shop, and put it under his coat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1416" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1416" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1416" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1416" type="given" value="THOMAS BARNS"></interp>THOMAS BARNS THOMPSON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 12.) I went into the public-house and saw the prisoner eating the bacon—I said, "What is this?"—he said, "Some I brought from London with me"—I said, some had been taken from Mr. Clark's shop—this is Mr. Groves the Magutrate's handwriting—(<hi rend="italic">read</hi>)—"The prisoner says, 'I stole the bacon because I was hungry.'"</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's defence.</hi> I did not take it; while I was waiting in the room, an old lady opposite said, if you say you took it because you were hungry they will let you off, that is the reason I said so.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
